			body: '<!---\r\nThanks for creating a Pull Request üíñ!\r\n\r\nPlease read the following before submitting:\r\n- PRs that adds new external dependencies might take a while to review.\r\n- Keep your PR as small as possible.\r\n- Limit your PR to one type (docs, feature, refactoring, ci, or bugfix)\r\n-->\r\n\r\nCloses # [7740](https://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/issues/7740)\r\n\r\n## üìù Description\r\nThis PR fixes and issue where the `color` prop was merged with the final `__css` prop when rendering an `Icon` component. In the event that the `__css` prop includes a `color` property, the `__css` prop color would take priority as it is spread following the color prop in the `Icon` style object:\r\n\r\n[Icon Styles](https://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/blob/2456a7090439ebd1a1d1cdee36daa472d12ce6f7/packages/components/icon/src/icon.tsx#LL57C3-L66C4)\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst styles: SystemStyleObject = {\r\n    w: "1em",\r\n    h: "1em",\r\n    display: "inline-block",\r\n    lineHeight: "1em",\r\n    flexShrink: 0,\r\n    color,\r\n    ...__css,\r\n    ...customStyles,\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\n## ‚õ≥Ô∏è Current behavior (updates)\r\nWhen an `<Icon />`  component is given both a `__css` prop which includes a color property, as well as a `color` prop, the `__css` prop color value will take priority.\r\n\r\n## üöÄ New behavior\r\nIf both props are provided, the `color` prop will take priority\r\n\r\n## üí£ Is this a breaking change (Yes/No):\r\nNo\r\n\r\n## üìù Additional Information\r\n',
