			active_lock_reason: null,
			body: "### Description\r\n\r\nChakra-UI currently provides a Divider component for visually separating content, but it requires manual placement within the container component. This proposal suggests adding a container-level divide utility to Chakra-UI, allowing developers to easily add dividers between child elements without the need for manual placement of Divider components.\r\n\r\n### Problem Statement/Justification\r\n\r\nCurrently, when developers want to add dividers between elements, they have to manually insert Divider components at appropriate locations within the container component. This process leads to additional code complexity.\r\n\r\n## Proposed Solution or API\r\n\r\n### Introduce Divide Utility\r\n\r\nImplement a new utility class, such as divide-y, to add a vertical divider between child elements. This class should apply a border style to the bottom of each element, creating a visually distinct separation.\r\n\r\n### Customization Options\r\n\r\nProvide flexibility for customizing the appearance of dividers. Allow developers to specify the color, thickness, and style of the dividers through additional utility classes or theme configuration options.\r\n\r\n### API\r\n\r\nEnsure that the Divide utility adheres to Chakra-UI's existing API and naming conventions. Follow a syntax that is intuitive and aligns with the rest of the framework, making it easy for developers to understand and use.\r\n\r\n### Theme Customization\r\n\r\nIntroduce a new theme key, such as `divideColor`, to control the default color of dividers.\r\n\r\n### Responsiveness\r\n\r\nGenerate responsive variants for the Divide utility by default, enabling developers to adjust the behavior of dividers based on different screen sizes.\r\n\r\n### Alternatives\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/pull/1584",
