			active_lock_reason: null,
			body: "### Description\r\n\r\nWhen I pass both the `__css` and the `color` prop to the `Icon` component, I expect `color` to have higher priority, but `__css` wins.\r\n\r\nFrom the docs here (emphasis mine) https://chakra-ui.com/docs/styled-system/component-style#return-value:\r\n\r\n> Please note that we are passing the styles to the prop __css. It has the same API as [the sx prop](https://chakra-ui.com/docs/styled-system/the-sx-prop), **but has a lower style priority**. This means **you can override the style properties with chakra style props**.\r\n\r\nBut the following renders a red icon:\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\n<PhoneIcon color=\"blue\" __css={{ color: 'red' }}/>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Link to Reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/crazy-banzai-9c3yl9?file=/src/index.tsx\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nJust checking the rendered result is enough\r\n\r\n### Chakra UI Version\r\n\r\n2.0.18\r\n\r\n### Browser\r\n\r\nGoogle Chrome 114.0.5735.90\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\n- [X] macOS\r\n- [ ] Windows\r\n- [ ] Linux\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\nThe code does seem to do this intentionally, but I wonder if it was intended (I found this originally on Chakra 1, and saw the same behavior on Chakra 2)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/blob/2456a7090439ebd1a1d1cdee36daa472d12ce6f7/packages/components/icon/src/icon.tsx#L63-L64",
