			author_association: "NONE",
			active_lock_reason: null,
			body: "### Description\n\nDirectional CSS properties should be mapped to logical CSS properties by default. Additionally, shortcut versions of these properties should be used.\n\n### Problem Statement/Justification\n\n1. internally Chakra already uses logical CSS, which is great, but its styling API mostly highlights the old CSS syntax (e.g. marginRight ). So a developer, who isn't fit with the new CSS logical syntax, would be tempted to use the older non-logical syntax. In LTR, this wouldn't make a difference, but in RTL or other writing-modes, the mix of logical CSS properties and conventional properties will likely break the UI components.\r\n2. use of logical CSS shortcut syntax - this would reduce the amount of css applied + opens up new possibilities - e.g like `inset` \n\n### Proposed Solution or API\n\n1. in the core/styled-system configs, the old directional CSS props should be mapped to logical CSS by default\r\n2. shortcut syntax used - e.g `paddingX` should map to `paddingInline` instead of `paddingInlineStart` and `paddingInlineEnd`\n\n### Alternatives\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional Information\n\n_No response_",
