			body: "### Description\n\nPer ARIA specifications, `Modal` and `Drawer` dialogs should always return focus when they close back to the element that triggered the opening of the respective dialog. Unfortunately, that does not appear to work in all cases.\r\n\r\n- If the trigger element is inside a `TabPanel`, the focus does not get returned to the element but to the tab content, causing a page scroll up in Safari. Strangely enough, this issue occurs *only when clicking the trigger button with a mouse pointer*, rather than using keyboard only (Control+Tab and hitting enter when focused on the trigger button).\r\n- If the trigger element is inside another `Modal`/`Drawer`, opening another dialog, the focus gets returned back to the previous modal's close button instead of the original trigger element. This occurs regardless using mouse pointer or keyboard navigation, with the scroll glitch present in all browsers I tested.\r\n\r\n**Expected Behavior**\r\nThe focus should always be returned to the trigger element when using keyboard navigation (or page body when using mouse pointer) and not cause any unexpected page scroll jumps if there is a lot of content on the page.\n\n### Link to Reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/chakra-disclosure-focus-c1jeko?file=/App.tsx\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOpen the CodeSandbox and observe the following examples of the focus return issues:\r\n\r\n1. **Opening modal inside/outside the tab content** (Safari only)\r\n    - Scroll down and click the first of the two buttons (inside `TabPanel`) to open a modal.\r\n    - Close the modal and notice the page scrolls up to the top of the `TabPanel`.\r\n    - Scroll down again and try opening/closing the second trigger button (outside `TabPanel`). Close the modal and notice there are no scroll issues and that the page stays in place as it should.\r\n\r\n2. **Opening modal from another modal content** (All browsers)\r\n     - Toggle the second tab to reveal the second example button, and click it to open a modal dialog.\r\n     - Scroll down inside the modal and click the button to open additional content in another dialog.\r\n     - Close the additional content modal and observe that the page jumps up.\n\n### Chakra UI Version\n\n2.7.0\n\n### Browser\n\nSafari 16.5\n\n### Operating System\n\n- [X] macOS\n- [ ] Windows\n- [ ] Linux\n\n### Additional Information\n\nThe same issues occur both for `Modal` and `Drawer` components. I suspect this is caused by the dialogs trying to return the focus to the trigger element but perhaps unable to do so due to some additional overlay content (tabs or another disclosure element) that gets in the way.\r\n\r\nThe first example/scroll issue occurs only in Safari, while the second example also in other browsers, including Chrome 114 and Firefox 113.",
