			author_association: "NONE",
			active_lock_reason: null,
			body: "### Description\n\nWhen you are using 2 modals or Drawer and inside that drawer you can open a modal it breaks the scroll on the body of the 2nd modal.\r\n\r\nI've found other topics in issues, but they are workarounds which are not good solutions for a11y and overall functionality.\r\n\r\nTopics I've found:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/issues/7588 -> Talking about adding the other modal/drawer inside the first one, this seems to be good in practice, but let's say I want to re-use that modal throughout my project in different pages and want to control the opening/closing of it globally. In this case, I would like to store the `Modal` element somewhere once and use `context` to control it.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/issues/7356 -> Adding `blockScrollOnMount` to 1st `Modal` is not a good solution either, because the content scrolls behind the modal when you are scrolling.\r\n\r\n... and other topics that are talking about similar cases. So my question is were we using two modals on top of each other wrong this whole time and after `@chakra-ui/react@2.4.8` version upgrade it's intended to wrap your 2nd modal inside 1st?\n\n### Link to Reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/focused-night-qz8ne6?file=/src/index.tsx\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Click on open Modal \r\n2. Click on Open Modal 2\r\n3. try to scroll\r\n\r\n\r\nAdditional Info: you can downgrade it to `2.4.7` version and you won't see this issue but anything past this version breaks scroll.\r\n\n\n### Chakra UI Version\n\n2.6.1\n\n### Browser\n\nGoogle Chrome\n\n### Operating System\n\n- [X] macOS\n- [X] Windows\n- [ ] Linux\n\n### Additional Information\n\n_No response_",
