			active_lock_reason: null,
			body: '### Description\r\n\r\nWhen I move an `Input` from inside and `InputGroup` into it\'s own component, it loses the styling I\'d expect it to have for being inside an `InputGroup`.\r\n\r\nExample code and output below: \r\n```ts\r\nimport { Input, type InputProps } from "@chakra-ui/react";\r\nimport type { Control, FieldPath, FieldValues } from "react-hook-form";\r\nimport { useController } from "react-hook-form";\r\nimport { useIMask } from "react-imask";\r\n\r\ninterface MaskInputProps<\r\n  TFieldValues extends FieldValues = FieldValues,\r\n  TName extends FieldPath<TFieldValues> = FieldPath<TFieldValues>\r\n> extends InputProps {\r\n  control: Control<TFieldValues>;\r\n  name: TName;\r\n}\r\n\r\nconst MaskInput = <\r\n  TFieldValues extends FieldValues = FieldValues,\r\n  TName extends FieldPath<TFieldValues> = FieldPath<TFieldValues>\r\n>({\r\n  control,\r\n  name,\r\n  ...props\r\n}: MaskInputProps<TFieldValues, TName>) => {\r\n  const {\r\n    field: { onChange, ...field },\r\n  } = useController({\r\n    name,\r\n    control,\r\n  });\r\n\r\n  const { ref } = useIMask(\r\n    {\r\n      mask: Number,\r\n      thousandsSeparator: ",",\r\n      unmask: true,\r\n      radix: ".",\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      onAccept: (val: string) => {\r\n        onChange(val);\r\n      },\r\n    }\r\n  );\r\n\r\n  return <Input {...props} {...field} ref={ref} />;\r\n};\r\n\r\n// Hack to get the `InputGroup` styling to work\r\n// see https://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/blob/main/packages/components/input/src/input-group.tsx\r\n// and https://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/blob/2f7e044f5cc08e1a892dc57288f97a688ee729ec/packages/components/input/src/input.tsx#L71\r\nMaskInput.id = "Input";\r\n\r\nexport default MaskInput;\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\n<FormControl isInvalid={!!errors.amount}>\r\n  <FormLabel>Amount</FormLabel>\r\n  <InputGroup>\r\n    <InputLeftAddon>$</InputLeftAddon>\r\n    <MaskInput\r\n      control={control}\r\n      name="amount"\r\n      pattern="[0-9]*"\r\n      inputMode="numeric"\r\n    />\r\n  </InputGroup>\r\n  <FormErrorMessage>\r\n    Amount is required and must be a positive number\r\n  </FormErrorMessage>\r\n</FormControl>\r\n```\r\n<img width="499" alt="Screenshot 2023-05-30 at 2 27 34 PM" src="https://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/assets/8886318/40f8a7bb-a26a-44ba-8a58-62579b393d4b">\r\n\r\n<img width="692" alt="Screenshot 2023-05-30 at 2 24 22 PM" src="https://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/assets/8886318/074ecb95-912b-4923-b2c0-66853375b5f7">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Link to Reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/wizardly-robinson-nkjtjt?file=/src/index.tsx\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/wizardly-robinson-nkjtjt?file=/src/index.tsx\r\n2. Focus both text boxes\r\n3. Notice styling issues\r\n\r\n\r\n### Chakra UI Version\r\n\r\n2.6.1\r\n\r\n### Browser\r\n\r\nChrome 113\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\n- [X] macOS\r\n- [ ] Windows\r\n- [ ] Linux\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n_No response_',
