			active_lock_reason: null,
			body: "### Description\r\n\r\nWhen I create a Drawer without having a DrawerHeader as a child of DrawerContent, the DrawerCloseButton appears to be normal visually, but can only be clicked on its right side in some cases. The hover behavior of the DrawerCloseButton also only applies when the cursor is hovering over the right side of the button in these cases.\r\n\r\nThis happens when an Input Element is used as a child of the DrawerBody component, but I have not checked extensively to see if it happens when using other elements as well.\r\n\r\nIf DrawerHeader is a required child or DrawerContent, I failed to see it in the documentation. Should there be some kind of default behavior if no DrawerHeader is used?\r\n\r\n### Link to Reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/zealous-davinci-t6945z\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to [this example](https://codesandbox.io/s/zealous-davinci-t6945z)\r\n2. When the example finishes loading, click on Open Drawer\r\n3. Hover/Click the left side of the DrawerCloseButton\r\n4. Check intended behaviors\r\n5. Hover/Click the right side of the DrawerCloseButton\r\n6. Check intended behaviors\r\n\r\n\r\n### Chakra UI Version\r\n\r\n2.5.1\r\n\r\n### Browser\r\n\r\nGoogle Chrome 113.0.5672.127\r\nFirefox 102.11.0esr\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\n- [ ] macOS\r\n- [X] Windows\r\n- [ ] Linux\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n_No response_",
